article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 59, Ball St. 41
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Michael Bramos fueled a 16-3 run in the second half as Miami of Ohio easily defeated Ball State at home Wednesday night, 59-41. Bramos was the game's top scorer with 14 points, and Tyler Dierkers added 12 points and six rebounds for Miami (13-7, 6-2 Mid-American Conference). The RedHawks had a slim 25-22 lead at half time over Ball State (10-10, 5-3). With 11:47 left in the game, Bramos scored 10 of Miami's next 16 points and pushed the lead to 49-31 with 5:27 left. Ball State's Brandon Lampley had 10 points and five rebounds. Ball State had 17 turnovers, compared to Miami's nine.
